title: Weekly Market
description: Once-day-a-week market for the local Burmese, Chinese, and Muslim community. Lots of inexpensive vegan food and snacks like veg samosa, fried rice, pakora, chapati, corn cake, semolina cake (contains honey), Burmese tofu fritter, Burmese black sticky rice donut with jaggery syrup. Also vendors selling fresh fruit and vegetable, juices, Burmese pickles, fresh tofu, and tofu packed in chilli and oil, and others. Location is behind the mosque, follow the sign.
